Preheat your oven to 220°C and put a large #saucepan{} of water with a pinch of @salt{} on to boil. Peel and chop the @potato{2} into 2cm chunks. Pop them into your #pan{} of boiling water and simmer until cooked, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> TIP: The potato is cooked when you can easily slip a knife through.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @British pork mince{600%g} with a pinch of @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Fry until browned, about ~{5%minutes}. Use a #wooden spoon{} to break it up as it cooks. Once browned, pour in the @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1}, @water{100%ml}, @tomato ketchup{2%tbsp} and @chicken stock pot{1}. Stir well to dissolve the stock pot.

If you think your kids will like the herby seasoning, add the @?Italian style herbs{2.5%tsp} in now (just leave them out if not). Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to medium and simmer until the mixture has reduced by half and is thick and tomatoey, ~{12-15%minutes}. Stir occasionally, reducing the heat if necessary.

Once the potato is cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to your pan off the heat. Add the @unsalted butter{60%g}, a pinch of @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Mash with a #potato masher{} (or fork) until smooth. Once the pork mixture is thickened, pour it into an #ovenproof dish{} and top with dollops of mashed potato. Spread out the potato so it covers the whole top, then sprinkle over the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}. Bake in your oven until golden, ~{15-20%minutes}.

While the pie cooks, put another large #saucepan{} of water with a pinch of @salt{} on to boil and then finish your washing up (or have a sit down!). ~{5%minutes} before the pie is ready, add the @mangetout{2} and @peas{1%100g} to your pan of boiling water and simmer until cooked, ~{5%minutes}. When ready, drain the veggies in your colander.

Spoon the pie into bowls with the mangetout and peas alongside. Enjoy!